Russians shells villages close to the town of Soledar, the scene of intense battles in recent weeks.

Russian forces were shelling villages close to the town of Soledar in Ukraine’s east, the Ukrainian authorities said on Wednesday, as Moscow pressed ahead with its campaign to encircle and capture the nearby city of Bakhmut, the site of some of the fiercest recent battles in the war. Read more

